It may introduce an SQL injection risk.
Line 45: Comment says "Upsert user", but code only performs only plain INSERT.
Lines 37-50: Database connection never explicitly closed. I would use try/finally pattern so connection is always closed.
Line 42: Storing full raw payload may help with debugging but may store sensitive data.
Line 10: Production code will fail if webhook secret is missing.
Line 55: Deployment should use a production WSGI server.

